
GS1 is leading the retail industry's transition to 2D barcodes at the point of sale (POS). During this transition period,  items may be marked with both a 1D barcode and a 2D barcode. To prevent transaction errors, such as the double-counting of a single item, scanners must be configured to properly decode items that have multiple barcodes. This capability is essential to ensure a seamless checkout process with minimal disruption to end-user workflow and productivity.
<br /><br />
<b>GS1 Compliant Retail Barcodes</b><br />

Only the following barcode symbologies are approved for identifying trade items in retail POS applications. All GS1 compliant retail barcodes must contain a Global Trade Item Number (GTIN) as the primary identifier.
