    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding: 8px;">EAN-8</td>
      <td style="padding: 8px;"></td>
      <td style="padding: 8px;"></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<br />
<b>Data Transmission Rules</b><br />
The following rules describe the scanner's default behavior for data transmission:<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• <b>Data Order:</b> The GTIN is always transmitted as the first data field in the output.<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• <b>GS1 Digital Link Conversion:</b> The scanner automatically converts GS1 Digital Link URI syntax to the corresponding GS1 element string syntax:<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• “Data Matrix with GS1 Digital Link URI” is transmitted as code type “GS1 Data Matrix”.<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• “QR Code with GS1 Digital Link URI” is transmitted as code type “GS1 QR Code”.<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• <b>GTIN Formatting:</b><br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• For <b>DataBar</b> and <b>2D</b> symbols, the GTIN is transmitted with its Application Identifier (AI) and padded with leading zeros to 14 digits (e.g., “0100134567890123”).<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• For <b>UPC/EAN</b> barcodes, the GTIN is transmitted without an AI.<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• <b>Additional Data:</b><br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• Any remaining data in the barcode is transmitted according to user-configurable parsing and formatting rules, except with Mode 1.<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• By default, the scanner only transmits the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are present in the scanned barcode, regardless of the configured parsing rules.
<br /><br />
