<br />

<b>GS1 Digital Link Decoder Parameters</b>

<table style="width:100%" border="1" padding="5px">
  <tr bgcolor="#dce8ef">
    <th><center>Decoder Param</center></th>
    <th><center>Param Option/Description</center></th>
    <th><center>Param Name</center></th>
    <th><center>Param Value</center></th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>GS1 Digital Link Mode</td>
    <td><b>Mode 1:</b><br />The first barcode decoded is transmitted, regardless of type.<br /><br />
    <b>Mode 2:</b><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• If 1D barcode is the only barcode scanned, then only the GTIN is transmitted.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• If 2D barcode is decoded within the timeout period, then GTIN and other GS1 element strings are transmitted.<br /><br />
    <b>Mode 3:</b><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• If 1D barcode is decoded first, it waits for the 2D barcode to be decoded within the timeout period before reporting.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• If 2D barcode is decoded first, it immediately reports the barcode.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;• The scanner adds an 8-digit prefix (Label ID) that links matching 1D and 2D barcodes.</td>
    <td>decoder_gs1_digital_link_mode</td>
    <td>1 - Mode 1 (default)<br />2 - Mode 2<br />3 - Mode 3</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>GS1 Digital Link Prioritization Timeout</td>
    <td>The maximum amount of time the scanner attempts to decode a 2D GS1 Digital Link barcode. Default: 200 milliseconds</td>
    <td>decoder_gs1_digital_link_prioritization_timeout</td>
    <td>100-3000 milliseconds</td>
  </tr>
</table>